	details = <
		["nb"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::nb]>
			purpose = <"For å registrere informasjon om et individs nåværende overordnede sysselsettingskategori og fritekstinformasjon om sysselsettingshistorikk.">
			use = <"Brukes for å registrere informasjon om et individs nåværende overordnede sysselsettingskategori og fritekstinformasjon om sysselsettingshistorikk.

Arketypen er laget for å benyttes i SLOTet \"Detaljer\" i arketypenEVALUATION.social_summary (Sosialanamnese), men kan også brukes innen eller andre ENTRY- eller CLUSTER-arketyper der det er klinisk relevant. Arketypen er i tillegg laget for å kunne inneholde arketypen CLUSTER.occupation_episode i SLOTet \"Sysselsettingsepisoder\" for å kunne beskrive detaljer rundt hver sysselsettingsepisode.">
			keywords = <"arbeid", "arbeidstaker", "arbeidsgiver", "arbeidsforhold", "arbeidshistorikk", "jobb", "ansatt", "yrke", "arbeidsløs", "studerer", "student", "elev", "trygdet", "ufør", "arbeidssituasjon", "erverv", "yrkestilknytning", "pensjon", "pensjonist", "attføring", "bransje", "arbeidsledig", "hjemmeværende", "stilling", "profesjon">
			misuse = <"Brukes ikke for å registrere strukturert informasjon om nåværende eller tidligere sysselsettingsepisoder. Bruk arketypen CLUSTER.occupation_episode for dette formålet.
	
Brukes ikke for å beskrive helserisikoer eller eksponering for farlige substanser i arbeidssituasjonen. Til dette brukes henholdsvis arketypene EVALUATION.health_risk eller EVALUATION.exposure.

Brukes ikke for å registrere informasjon om individets inntektskilder eller detaljer om inntekt.">
		>
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"To record an overview of the activities or services carried out by an individual over their lifetime that document their role in and contribution to society.">
			use = <"Use to record an overview of the activities or services carried out by an individual over their lifetime that document their role in, and contribution to, society. 

There are three main categories of occupation:
- Employment - formal work or a job which can be characterised by many parameters: paid or unpaid; full-or part-time; regular or irregular;
- Actively seeking employment; or 
- Not seeking employment - for example: children; students; retirees; and those unable to work.

This archetype has been specifically designed to be used in the 'Details' SLOT within the EVALUATION.social_summary archetype, but can also be used within any other ENTRY or CLUSTER archetypes, where clinically appropriate. In addition, it has been designed to hold the CLUSTER.occupation_record in the 'Occupation record' SLOT in order to describe the detail for each occupation record or period.

For each role or contribution, use a separate instance of the CLUSTER.occupation_record in the Occupation record' SLOT.">
			keywords = <"employment", "study", "job", "work", "carer", "role", "pensioner", "student", "employee", "employer", "profession", "unemployment", "occupation", "child", "retiree">
			misuse = <"Not to be used for recording structured details about a specific role or contribution. Use the CLUSTER.occupation_record archetype within Óccupation record' SLOT for this purpose.

Not to be used for detailed descriptions of health risks or exposure to hazardous substances in the workplace. Use the EVALUATION.health_risk or EVALUATION.exposure archetype for these purposes.

Not to be used to record information about sources of income or income details for the individual. Use the CLUSTER.income_summary archetype for this purpose.">
			copyright = <"© openEHR Foundation">
		>
	>
